line_1: The scenes to which not youth alone resorts,
line_2: Her theatres, her revels, and her sports,

line_1: Who fliest the busy, full resorts
For whom, retir'd, I shun the gay resorts
line_2: Of sportful cities, and of pompous courts;

line_1: You she preferr'd to all the gay resorts
line_2: The pomp of cities, and the pride of courts.

line_1: To youth, to age, to every scene resorts.
line_2: He comes whilst youth her shield of health supports;

line_1: For hidden sorrow with the great resorts.
line_2: Seek not the splendid cares of shining courts,
